investigation.title: Influence of gonadectomy on muscle health in micro- and partial-gravity environments in rats (Estrous Cycle Monitoring)
investigation.description: Gonadal hormones, such as testosterone and estradiol, modulate muscle size and strength in males and females. However, the influence of sex hormones on muscle strength in micro- and partial-gravity environments (e.g., the Moon or Mars) is not fully understood.

project.title: OS-891
project.funding: NASA Awards 80NSSC21K0311 (M.E.R.-C./S.B.R.) and 80NSSC19K9518 (S.B.R.) as well as NIH Award R37HD019938 (U.B.K.) and T32GM144273 (A.W.) from the National Institute of General Medical Sciences
